    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Reflections: Cheney, Vice Presidents and Texans</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Tom Gallucci letter agrees with George W Bush selection of Dick Cheney as running mate</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I agree that George W. Bush's choice of Dick Cheney as his running mate is revealing of Mr. Bush's approach to politics and to governing (''A Safe Pick Is Revealing,'' news analysis, front page, July 26). Governor Bush is indeed more concerned with governing than with politics, a quality of a true leader. He chose ability over flash. He is looking to develop a strong team to successfully lead the country rather than simply creating a political machine to garner votes.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I agree that George W. Bush's choice of Dick Cheney as his running mate is revealing of Mr. Bush's approach to politics and to governing (''A Safe Pick Is Revealing,'' news analysis, front page, July 26). Governor Bush is indeed more concerned with governing than with politics, a quality of a true leader. He chose ability over flash. He is looking to develop a strong team to successfully lead the country rather than simply creating a political machine to garner votes.</p>
        <p>I believe that the American people recognize substance over sizzle, and that a capable partner like Mr. Cheney will result in a political advantage and enhance Mr. Bush's chance for victory.</p>
        <p>TOM GALLUCCI  Point Lookout, N.Y., July 26, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
